The paper deals with the detection and characterization of symmetry in 3D shapes, which is a problem commonly studied in computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves techniques such as correspondence space voting and transformation space mapping, which are commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper introduces a novel cost matrix formulation, which could be of interest to researchers in machine learning (cs.LG) who work on developing new cost functions for optimization problems.
